This paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) category as it presents a method for automatic malware signature generation and classification. The paper also uses a deep belief network (DBN) implemented with a deep stack of denoising autoencoders, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) categories. Additionally, the paper's focus on deep learning and neural networks makes it likely to belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category. Finally, the paper's emphasis on the practical application of the method in malware detection and classification suggests that it could also belong to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) category.
